358.220.  Right to an account. — Any partner shall have the right to a formal account as to partnership affairs:
  (1)  If he is wrongfully excluded from the partnership business or possession of its property by his copartners;
  (2)  If the right exists under the terms of any agreement;
  (3)  As provided by section 358.210;
  (4)  Whenever other circumstances render it just and reasonable.
(L. 1949 p. 506 § 22)
